## Mental Model

**MRR is fragile unless pricing grows with value.**

Every product must include at least one expansion revenue lever. This is how you turn a $29/mo tool into a $290/mo business without acquisition cost. Pricing is not an afterthought—it's a core part of product design that must be considered before engineering begins.

Expansion revenue ensures that as customers succeed, their value (and revenue) grows naturally, creating durable MRR and reducing churn risk.
